WHAT IS ACCENT?
1. intonation(speech music)
2. liaisons(word connections) 
3. pronunciation(the spoken sounds of vowels, consonants, combinations)
unlike the grammar and vocabulary, Accent is free form, intuitive, and creative. So, thinking of music, feeling, and flow.


THREE WAYS TO CHANGE YOUR VOICE FOR INTONATION
1. Volume(speak louder)
2. Length(stretch out a word)
3. Pitch(change your tone)
